[According to a report issued by the State Veterinary Services on 29 Dec 2022, the current HPAI H5N1 epizootic started (date of diagnosis) on 21 Nov 2022 on a turkey fattening farm; until 28 Dec 2022, 6 additional outbreaks have been identified and culled: 4 turkey fattening farms (49 500 culled) and 2 broiler farms (198 000 culled). The said and additional information, including maps presenting the outbreaks' locations and the sites where 2 infected wild birds have been found, are available at https://bit.ly/3Qk0Zdk (in Hebrew).

The new event on a broiler breeding farm is cause for additional concern. Such farms maintain a most severe biosecurity regime, expected to provide protection. - Mod.AS

